WEBVTT

00:01.168 --> 00:05.838
Some stories attribute
great powers to the Moon.

00:05.873 --> 00:08.507
It does have some effect on us.

00:10.311 --> 00:11.610
Since the time

00:11.645 --> 00:14.313
of the very first Apollo Moon mission...

00:14.348 --> 00:15.647
The Eagle has landed.

00:15.683 --> 00:17.616
...researchers have pored over

00:17.651 --> 00:19.551
photos of the Moon

00:19.587 --> 00:21.286
looking for structures,

00:21.322 --> 00:24.323
and they found some unusual things.

00:24.358 --> 00:26.692
Only 300 kilometers away

00:26.727 --> 00:30.629
from where Apollo 11 ended up landing.

00:30.664 --> 00:34.767
This area has undeniable architecture

00:34.802 --> 00:36.702
that looks like what you would see

00:36.737 --> 00:38.203
from obelisks.

00:39.507 --> 00:40.773
Somebody built something

00:40.808 --> 00:43.709
on the Moon a long, long time ago.

00:43.744 --> 00:46.245
And I don't think it was earthlings.

00:47.948 --> 00:48.914
The entire object

00:48.949 --> 00:51.383
may be of artificial origin.

00:51.419 --> 00:53.485
My question is,

00:53.521 --> 00:55.220
who built the Moon?

00:55.256 --> 00:58.690
Since the dawn of civilization,

00:58.726 --> 01:02.895
mankind has credited its origins to gods

01:02.930 --> 01:05.764
and other visitors from the stars.

01:05.800 --> 01:07.866
What if it were true?

01:07.902 --> 01:10.702
Did extraterrestrial beings

01:10.738 --> 01:14.273
really help to shape our history?

01:14.308 --> 01:16.475
And if so...

01:16.510 --> 01:20.612
might the answer be found
not on Earth but on the Moon?

